Italy lira touches two - year high vs mark at 986 . 65 . The Italian lira firmed past its 990 per mark ERM central parity rate on Thursday to touch an over two - year quoted high of 986 . 65 per mark boosted by dollar strength , Milan dealers said . The lira ' s previous high against the mark was set in the first week of July 1994 when it touched 984 . 00 . At 1255 GMT , the lira was at a screen quoted 987 . 40 / 7 . 70 per mark . " The movement of the lira is being dictated by that of the dollar , " one dealer said , noting the dollar ' s rise on calls by Bank of France monetary council member Jean - Pierre Gerard for a stronger U . S . currency . - - Milan newsroom + 392 66129589 
